   261	## Trust Boundaries
   262	
   263	| Boundary | Description |
   264	|----------|-------------|
   265	| RAW file -> writer | Thermo RAW is parsed by trusted, already-shipping TRFP reader code (reused, not new) |
   266	| writer -> .mzpeak archive | New code constructs Parquet + zip bytes consumed by external readers |
   267	| .mzpeak -> reference reader | OPEN gate runs an external Python process over the produced file |
   268	
   269	## STRIDE Threat Register
   270	
   271	| Threat ID | Category | Component | Disposition | Mitigation Plan |
   272	|-----------|----------|-----------|-------------|-----------------|
   273	| T-01-01 | Tampering | mzpeak_index.json lists a facet not actually written | mitigate | Emit JSON listing EXACTLY the two facets written; reader fails OPEN otherwise |
   274	| T-01-02 | Denial of Service | Zero-point first spectrum -> empty/invalid facet | mitigate | If point count is 0, write one honest base-peak point rather than an empty column |
   275	| T-01-03 | Information Disclosure | Accidental deflate (CompressionLevel default) breaks STORED contract | mitigate | Force `CompressionLevel.NoCompression`; verify `compress_type==0` in the gate |
   276	| T-01-SC | Tampering | npm/pip/cargo installs | accept | No new C# NuGet packages (Parquet.Net/Newtonsoft already deps). Only pip installs are `pynumpress`/`psims` into the local test env, verified on pypi.org during research; not shipped in output |
   277	</threat_model>
