   212	## Unknown 3 — Reference reader OPEN gate — DECISION: Python `MzPeakFile(...)` one-liner, exit code = gate
   213	
   214	**Cheapest reliable OPEN gate** (self-contained, no Rust build). [VERIFIED: run against both the
   215	minimal spike archive and the real reference archive]
   216	
   217	```bash
   218	PYTHONPATH=refs/mzPeak/python python3.11 -c "
   219	import numpy, numpy.typing
   220	from mzpeak import MzPeakFile
   221	f = MzPeakFile('OUTPUT.mzpeak')
   222	assert f.spectrum_metadata is not None and len(f.spectrum_metadata) >= 1
   223	print('OPEN OK', len(f.spectrum_metadata))
   224	"
   225	```
   226	- Exit 0 = archive opened and the spectrum-metadata facet parsed.
   227	- Nonzero = failure (raises before the `print`).
   228	
   229	**Verification runs:**
   230	- Minimal spike archive → `OPEN OK 1`, exit 0.
   231	- Real `refs/mzPeak/small.mzpeak` (control) → `OPEN OK 48`, exit 0.
   232	
   233	**Environment requirements for the gate** (the system anaconda python3 is 3.7 and cannot run the
   234	`match`/`StrEnum` reader; use `python3.11`):
   235	- Python ≥ 3.11 (reader uses `match` statements and `StrEnum`).
   236	- `pyarrow`, `pandas`, `numpy` — present in the `python3.11` env [VERIFIED].
   237	- `pynumpress` and `psims` — hard top-level imports in the reader; installed via
   238	  `python3.11 -m pip install pynumpress psims` [VERIFIED: both installed and OPEN passed].
   239	- `import numpy.typing` must be forced before importing mzpeak (older numpy build doesn't auto-load
   240	  the `typing` submodule) — included in the one-liner above. [VERIFIED]
   241	
   242	**Rust alternative (not recommended for the gate):** `cd refs/mzPeak && cargo r --example read -- OUTPUT.mzpeak`
   243	opens via `ArchiveReader`/`MzPeakReader` but requires a full Rust build of the workspace and is slower
   244	to invoke. Prefer the Python path. (For an even cheaper *structural* pre-check that needs no mzpeak
   245	deps: `python3 -c "import zipfile,json; z=zipfile.ZipFile('OUTPUT.mzpeak'); assert all(i.compress_type==0 for i in z.infolist()); json.load(z.open('mzpeak_index.json'))"` — but this only checks STORED+index, not reader acceptance.)
