   249	## Unknown 4 — mzpeak_index.json minimum — DECISION: 2 file entries, empty metadata block
   250	
   251	[VERIFIED: schema/mzpeak_index.json requires only `files` + `metadata`; reader `_from_zip_archive`
   252	keys on `entity_type`/`data_kind`; OPEN succeeded with the JSON below]
   253	
   254	The JSON schema (`refs/mzPeak/schema/mzpeak_index.json`) requires exactly two top-level keys:
   255	`files` (array) and `metadata` (object, `additionalProperties: true` → **may be `{}`**). Each file
   256	entry needs `name`, `entity_type`, `data_kind`. The reader matches on the `(EntityType, DataKind)`
   257	tuple to decide which facet reader to construct (`reader.py` `_from_zip_archive` / `file_index.py`).
   258	
   259	**Minimal index for OPEN** (the metadata block may be empty for the skeleton):
   260	```json
   261	{
   262	  "files": [
   263	    { "name": "spectra_data.parquet",     "entity_type": "spectrum", "data_kind": "data arrays" },
   264	    { "name": "spectra_metadata.parquet", "entity_type": "spectrum", "data_kind": "metadata" }
   265	  ],
   266	  "metadata": {}
   267	}
   268	```
   269	
   270	**Reader OPEN actually requires** (beyond the index file itself):
   271	- `mzpeak_index.json` MUST exist in the zip, else `FileNotFoundError` (reader `_from_zip_archive`).
   272	- A `(spectrum, metadata)` facet — the reader builds `MzPeakSpectrumMetadataReader`, which reads
   273	  KV-metadata keys `spectrum_count` and `spectrum_data_point_count` from that Parquet (both required,
   274	  else `IndexError`/`KeyError`). The `spectrum` struct must have an `index` leaf
   275	  (`path_in_schema == "spectrum.index"`). [VERIFIED]
   276	- A `(spectrum, data arrays)` facet — builds `MzPeakArrayDataReader`, which reads the
   277	  `spectrum_array_index` KV-metadata JSON (`{"prefix":"point","entries":[...]}`) and `spectrum_count`.
   278	  [VERIFIED: spike supplied this and OPEN passed]
   279	- Valid `entity_type`/`data_kind` strings: `spectrum`/`chromatogram` and
   280	  `data arrays`/`metadata`/`peaks` (exact lowercase strings) [VERIFIED: file_index.py StrEnums].
   281	
   282	> Insight: only **list the facets you actually write**. Listing a facet in `files[]` that doesn't
   283	> exist (or lacks its required KV keys) makes the reader try to construct that facet reader and fail.
   284	> For the skeleton, write exactly the two facets above and list exactly those two.
   285	
   286	**KV metadata keys the reader needs** (set via `writer.CustomMetadata`):
   287	
   288	| Facet | Required KV keys | Spike value used |
   289	|-------|------------------|------------------|
   290	| spectra_metadata.parquet | `spectrum_count`, `spectrum_data_point_count` | "1", "3" |
   291	| spectra_data.parquet | `spectrum_array_index` (JSON), `spectrum_count`, `spectrum_data_point_count` | see below |
   292	
   293	`spectrum_array_index` minimal value that opened (entries describe the m/z + intensity arrays):
   294	```json
   295	{"prefix":"point","entries":[
   296	  {"context":"spectrum","path":"point.mz","data_type":"MS:1000523","array_type":"MS:1000514",
   297	   "array_name":"m/z array","unit":"MS:1000040","buffer_format":"point","buffer_priority":"primary"},
   298	  {"context":"spectrum","path":"point.intensity","data_type":"MS:1000521","array_type":"MS:1000515",
   299	   "array_name":"intensity array","unit":"MS:1000131","buffer_format":"point","buffer_priority":"primary"}
   300	]}
   301	```
