   304	
   305	## Unknown 5 — ZIP STORED — DECISION: ZipArchive + CompressionLevel.NoCompression (verified STORED)
   306	
   307	[VERIFIED: spike zip inspected — all entries `compress_type=0` (STORED); reference reader opened it]
   308	
   309	```csharp
   310	using var zip = ZipFile.Open(outputPath, ZipArchiveMode.Create);
   311	void AddStored(string name, byte[] bytes) {
   312	    var entry = zip.CreateEntry(name, CompressionLevel.NoCompression);  // -> STORED
   313	    using var s = entry.Open();
   314	    s.Write(bytes, 0, bytes.Length);
   315	}
   316	AddStored("mzpeak_index.json", indexJsonBytes);
   317	AddStored("spectra_data.parquet", dataParquetBytes);
   318	AddStored("spectra_metadata.parquet", metaParquetBytes);
   319	```
   320	
   321	**Gotcha confirmed false here:** in .NET 8, `CompressionLevel.NoCompression` does produce a true
   322	STORED entry (method 0), not a deflate-with-level-0 entry. The spike's three entries all reported
   323	`compress_type=0` via Python `zipfile`. [VERIFIED]
   324	
   325	**Reference reader treats the zip as a directory-of-parquet:** `reader.py` opens the zip with
   326	`zipfile.ZipFile`, reads `mzpeak_index.json`, then `archive.open(name)` each listed parquet and wraps
   327	it in `pa.PythonFile`. It also supports an unpacked directory (`small.unpacked.mzpeak/`). [VERIFIED:
   328	reader.py `_from_zip_archive` / `_from_directory`]
   329	
   330	> Practical note: build each Parquet facet fully in a `MemoryStream` first (Parquet.Net writes its
   331	> footer on dispose / needs a seekable stream), then write the finished bytes into the STORED zip
   332	> entry. Do not hand Parquet.Net the zip entry stream directly (zip entry streams are not seekable).
   333	
