   336	## Unknown 6 — TRFP wiring specifics — DECISION: exact insertion points confirmed
   337	
   338	All file:line references [VERIFIED: read from source].
   339	
   340	**Writer constructor signature the new writer must match** (all existing writers use the identical
   341	one-arg ctor delegating to the base):
   342	```csharp
   343	public MzPeakSpectrumWriter(ParseInput parseInput) : base(parseInput) { }
   344	```
   345	- `MgfSpectrumWriter(ParseInput)`  — `Writer/MgfSpectrumWriter.cs:20`
   346	- `MzMlSpectrumWriter(ParseInput)` — `Writer/MzMlSpectrumWriter.cs:55`
   347	- `ParquetSpectrumWriter(ParseInput)` — `Writer/ParquetSpectrumWriter.cs:43`
   348	- base: `protected SpectrumWriter(ParseInput parseInput)` — `Writer/SpectrumWriter.cs:63`
   349	- abstract method to override: `public abstract void Write(IRawDataPlus rawFile, int firstScanNumber, int lastScanNumber)` — `Writer/SpectrumWriter.cs:72`
   350	
   351	**1. Enum value** — `OutputFormat.cs` (current enum: `MGF, MzML, IndexMzML, Parquet, None`).
   352	Insert `MzPeak` **before `None`** to keep `None`'s ordinal meaning stable in help text. New ordinal: 4.
   353	```csharp
   354	public enum OutputFormat { MGF, MzML, IndexMzML, Parquet, MzPeak, None }
   355	```
   356	Numbering ripple: `None` moves from 4 → 5. Help text below must reflect this.
   357	
   358	**2. Help text** — `MainClass.cs:530-531` (`"f=|format="` option description). Current:
   359	> "The spectra output format: 0 for MGF, 1 for mzML, 2 for indexed mzML, 3 for Parquet, 4 for None ...".
   360	Update to include `4 for mzPeak, 5 for None`. (Format string is text/numeric tolerant; `ParseToEnum`
   361	at `MainClass.cs:911` handles both name and int.)
   362	
   363	**3. Dispatch switch** — `RawFileParser.cs:169-184` (`switch (parseInput.OutputFormat)`).
   364	Add a case mirroring the Parquet case (lines 180-183):
   365	```csharp
   366	case OutputFormat.MzPeak:
   367	    spectrumWriter = new MzPeakSpectrumWriter(parseInput);
   368	    spectrumWriter.Write(rawFile, firstScanNumber, lastScanNumber);
   369	    break;
   370	```
   371	
   372	**4. Gzip suppression** — `MainClass.cs:776` currently forces `Gzip=false` for Parquet. Extend to
   373	also cover MzPeak (a STORED zip must never be gzip-wrapped):
   374	```csharp
   375	if (parseInput.OutputFormat == OutputFormat.Parquet ||
   376	    parseInput.OutputFormat == OutputFormat.MzPeak) parseInput.Gzip = false;
   377	```
   378	
   379	**5. Output stream / extension** — `SpectrumWriter.ConfigureWriter` (`Writer/SpectrumWriter.cs:78-103`)
   380	has a `OutputFormat.Parquet` branch (line 88) that creates a plain binary `File.Create` stream (no
   381	gzip, no text). Extend that condition to include `MzPeak`, then call `ConfigureWriter(".mzpeak")` from
   382	the new writer to get `Writer.BaseStream`, and write the finished STORED-zip bytes there (mirrors how
   383	`ParquetSpectrumWriter` writes to `Writer.BaseStream`). `NormalizeFileName` already yields the right
   384	`<rawname>.mzpeak` output path. Alternatively the writer can open its own `ZipFile` on the target path;
   385	either is acceptable, but reusing `ConfigureWriter` keeps stdout/StreamWriter lifecycle consistent.
   386	
   387	> Watch-out: `ConfigureWriter` wraps the stream in a `StreamWriter`. For binary zip output, write to
   388	> `Writer.BaseStream` (as ParquetSpectrumWriter does), then `Writer.Flush()`/`Writer.Close()`.
