     1	# Requirements: mzPeak Writer for ThermoRawFileParser
     2	
     3	**Defined:** 2026-06-14
     4	**Core Value:** Produce a spec-valid mzPeak archive readable by the reference readers, straight from Thermo RAW, without losing spectral information.
     5	
     6	## v1 Requirements
     7	
     8	### CLI Integration
     9	
    10	- [ ] **CLI-01**: `MzPeak` added to `OutputFormat` enum and selectable via `-f mzpeak` / `--format mzpeak`
    11	- [ ] **CLI-02**: `--format` help text lists mzPeak; output filename gets `.mzpeak` extension
    12	- [ ] **CLI-03**: `RawFileParser` dispatch instantiates `MzPeakSpectrumWriter` for the new format
    13	
    14	### Parquet Foundation
    15	
    16	- [ ] **PQ-01**: Write a Parquet file with nested structs + lists-of-structs using Parquet.Net (spike-validated approach)
    17	- [ ] **PQ-02**: Reusable helpers to build the repeated `PARAM` value-struct and CV-accession-named columns
    18	- [ ] **PQ-03**: Per-Parquet ZSTD compression; assemble facets into a STORED (uncompressed) ZIP archive
    19	
    20	### Spectra Data
    21	
    22	- [ ] **DATA-01**: `spectra_data.parquet` in point layout `struct<spectrum_index:u64, mz:f64, intensity:f32>`
    23	- [ ] **DATA-02**: m/z coerced to float64, intensity to float32; m/z sorted ascending per spectrum (multiset preserved)
    24	- [ ] **DATA-03**: Centroid peaks written to `spectra_peaks.parquet` when a centroid representation exists
    25	- [ ] **DATA-04**: MS-level / scan-range filtering honored (reuse `ParseInput` filters)
    26	
    27	### Spectra Metadata (packed parallel tables)
    28	
    29	- [ ] **META-01**: `spectrum` struct rows — index, id, ms_level, time, polarity, representation, type, observed m/z range, counts, base peak, TIC
    30	- [ ] **META-02**: `scan` struct rows — scan_start_time (minutes), filter_string, ion_injection_time, instrument_configuration_ref, scan_windows
    31	- [ ] **META-03**: `precursor` struct rows — isolation window (target/lower/upper offsets) + activation params
    32	- [ ] **META-04**: `selected_ion` struct rows — selected ion m/z, charge state, intensity
    33	- [ ] **META-05**: CV terms encoded as CURIEs via the established mzML-CV→mzPeak mapping table
    34	
    35	### File-Level Metadata & Index
    36	
    37	- [ ] **IDX-01**: `mzpeak_index.json` lists all present facets (`files[]`) with entity_type/data_kind
    38	- [ ] **IDX-02**: `metadata{}` block with instrument_configuration_list (ionsource/analyzer/detector + CV params) from Thermo instrument info via `OntologyMapping`
    39	- [ ] **IDX-03**: software_list (TRFP entry) and data_processing_method_list (conversion + any narrowing/sort provenance)
    40	- [ ] **IDX-04**: file_description (source RAW file, contents params) and cv_list (MS, UO)
    41	
    42	### Chromatograms
    43	
    44	- [ ] **CHROM-01**: `chromatograms_data.parquet` point layout `struct<chromatogram_index:u64, time:f64, intensity:f32, ms_level:i64>` with the TIC
    45	- [ ] **CHROM-02**: `chromatograms_metadata.parquet` with the chromatogram struct (type=TIC CURIE, polarity, point count)
    46	
    47	### Conformance & Verification
    48	
    49	- [ ] **VER-01**: Output archive opens in the reference Python mzPeak reader without error
    50	- [ ] **VER-02**: Spectrum count, per-spectrum peak counts, and (m/z,intensity) multiset round-trip vs. the source (within f32 intensity tolerance)
    51	- [ ] **VER-03**: NUnit test converts `ThermoRawFileParserTest/Data/small.RAW` to mzPeak and asserts archive structure + readability
    52	
    53	## v2 Requirements
    54	
    55	### Optimizations
    56	
    57	- **OPT-01**: Chunked layout with delta-encoded m/z chunks
    58	- **OPT-02**: Numpress (SLOF/linear) intensity/m/z compression
    59	- **OPT-03**: Null-marking / zero-run stripping for profile data
    60	- **OPT-04**: Ion-mobility (FAIMS) value + type columns populated
    61	- **OPT-05**: Profile + centroid dual emission (`spectra_data` profile, `spectra_peaks` centroid) for the same scan
