     1	# mzPeak ground-truth schema (extracted from refs/mzPeak/small.unpacked.mzpeak)
     2	
     3	Authoritative Arrow/Parquet schemas of a real mzPeak archive produced by the HUPO-PSI Rust
     4	writer. This is the *exact* target the TRFP C# writer must reproduce.
     5	
     6	## Archive layout (uncompressed ZIP, `CompressionMethod::Stored`)
     7	
     8	- `mzpeak_index.json` — `{ "files":[{name,entity_type,data_kind}], "metadata":{...} }`
     9	- `spectra_metadata.parquet` — packed parallel tables (REQUIRED)
    10	- `spectra_data.parquet` — point layout signal (REQUIRED)
    11	- `spectra_peaks.parquet` — point layout centroids (OPTIONAL)
    12	- `chromatograms_metadata.parquet` — (present when chromatograms exist)
    13	- `chromatograms_data.parquet`
    14	
    15	Per-Parquet ZSTD internal compression. CV terms encoded as `NS:accession` CURIEs; column
    16	names embed the accession, e.g. `MS_1000511_ms_level`.
    17	
    18	## spectra_data.parquet / spectra_peaks.parquet (point layout)
    19	
    20	```
    21	point: struct<spectrum_index: uint64, mz: double, intensity: float>
    22	```
    23	
    24	m/z = float64, intensity = float32. One row per data point. mz sorted ascending per spectrum.
    25	
    26	## chromatograms_data.parquet
    27	
    28	```
    29	point: struct<chromatogram_index: uint64, time: double, intensity: float, ms_level: int64>
    30	```
    31	
    32	## spectra_metadata.parquet — packed parallel tables
    33	
    34	Four independent TOP-LEVEL struct columns in one file. Each row populates exactly one;
    35	the others are null. (`scan`/`precursor`/`selected_ion` reference back via `source_index`.)
    36	
    37	### spectrum
    38	```
    39	index: uint64
    40	id: large_string
    41	MS_1000511_ms_level: uint8
    42	time: double
    43	MS_1000465_scan_polarity: int8
    44	MS_1000525_spectrum_representation: string   (CURIE: MS:1000127 centroid / MS:1000128 profile)
    45	MS_1000559_spectrum_type: string             (CURIE: MS:1000579 MS1 / MS:1000580 MSn)
    46	MS_1000528_lowest_observed_mz_unit_MS_1000040: double
    47	MS_1000527_highest_observed_mz_unit_MS_1000040: double
    48	MS_1003060_number_of_data_points: uint64
    49	MS_1003059_number_of_peaks: uint64
    50	MS_1000504_base_peak_mz_unit_MS_1000040: double
    51	MS_1000505_base_peak_intensity_unit_MS_1000131: float
    52	MS_1000285_total_ion_current_unit_MS_1000131: float
    53	data_processing_ref: large_string
    54	parameters: large_list<PARAM>
    55	auxiliary_arrays: large_list<AUX_ARRAY>
    56	number_of_auxiliary_arrays: uint32
    57	mz_delta_model: large_list<double>
    58	```
    59	
    60	### scan
    61	```
    62	source_index: uint64
    63	scan_index: uint64
    64	MS_1000016_scan_start_time_unit_UO_0000031: float   (UO:0000031 = minute)
    65	MS_1000616_preset_scan_configuration: uint32
    66	MS_1000512_filter_string: large_string
    67	MS_1000927_ion_injection_time_unit_UO_0000028: float
    68	ion_mobility_value: double
    69	ion_mobility_type: string
    70	instrument_configuration_ref: uint32
    71	spectrum_reference: large_string
    72	parameters: large_list<PARAM>
    73	scan_windows: large_list<struct<
    74	    MS_1000501_scan_window_lower_limit_unit_MS_1000040: float,
    75	    MS_1000500_scan_window_upper_limit_unit_MS_1000040: float,
    76	    parameters: large_list<PARAM>>>
    77	```
    78	
    79	### precursor
    80	```
    81	source_index: uint64
    82	precursor_index: uint64
    83	precursor_id: large_string
    84	isolation_window: struct<
    85	    MS_1000827_isolation_window_target_mz: float,
    86	    MS_1000828_isolation_window_lower_offset: float,
    87	    MS_1000829_isolation_window_upper_offset: float,
    88	    parameters: large_list<PARAM>>
    89	activation: struct<parameters: large_list<PARAM>>
    90	```
    91	
    92	### selected_ion
    93	```
    94	source_index: uint64
    95	precursor_index: uint64
    96	MS_1000744_selected_ion_mz_unit_MS_1000040: double
    97	MS_1000041_charge_state: int32
    98	MS_1000042_intensity_unit_MS_1000131: float
    99	ion_mobility_value: double
   100	ion_mobility_type: string
   101	parameters: large_list<PARAM>
   102	```
   103	
   104	## chromatograms_metadata.parquet
   105	
   106	```
   107	chromatogram: struct<index, id, MS_1000465_scan_polarity:int8,
   108	    MS_1000626_chromatogram_type:string, data_processing_ref,
   109	    MS_1003060_number_of_data_points:uint64, parameters, auxiliary_arrays,
   110	    number_of_auxiliary_arrays>
   111	precursor: struct<...>        (same shape as spectra precursor)
   112	selected_ion: struct<...>     (same shape as spectra selected_ion)
   113	```
   114	
   115	## PARAM (the repeated nested value type)
   116	
   117	```
   118	struct<
   119	  value: struct<integer:int64, float:double, string:large_string, boolean:bool>,  (union-as-struct, one set)
   120	  accession: string,   (CURIE, nullable)
   121	  name: large_string,
   122	  unit: string>        (CURIE, nullable)
   123	```
   124	
   125	## AUX_ARRAY
   126	```
   127	struct<data: large_list<uint8 not null>, name: PARAM, data_type: string,
   128	       compression: string, unit: string, parameters: large_list<PARAM>,
   129	       data_processing_ref: large_string>
   130	```
   131	
   132	## mzpeak_index.json metadata block (observed keys)
   133	`scan_settings_list`, `instrument_configuration_list` (components: ionsource/analyzer/detector
   134	with order + CV parameters), plus file_description / software_list / data_processing_method_list /
   135	sample_list / cv_list per the schema/ JSONSchemas.
   136	
   137	## Implementation notes / risks
   138	- Parquet.Net v5.0.1 is already a TRFP dependency. The existing ParquetSpectrumWriter uses the
   139	  high-level `ParquetSerializer.SerializeAsync` over a *flat* struct. mzPeak needs **nested
   140	  structs + lists-of-structs + parallel nullable top-level columns** — likely requires the
   141	  low-level Parquet.Net schema/column API (`ParquetSchema`, `DataColumn`, struct/list fields),
   142	  not the POCO serializer. This is the primary technical risk → warrants an early spike.
   143	- `large_string`/`large_list` = Arrow large variants (64-bit offsets). Confirm Parquet.Net maps
   144	  plain string/list compatibly (readers likely accept both); verify with a round-trip read.
   145	- ZIP must be STORED (no deflate) at the archive level.

