   194	- `ParseToEnum` (lines 911-940) generically handles both numeric and case-insensitive string (`Enum.Parse(enumType, s, true)`), so `-f mzpeak` and `-f 4` both resolve automatically once the enum member exists — **no change to ParseToEnum**.
   195	- **Change to copy:** line 776 disables gzip for `Parquet`. mzPeak is also a binary container — add an analogous guard: `if (parseInput.OutputFormat == OutputFormat.MzPeak) parseInput.Gzip = false;` (or fold into the existing condition).
   196	- **Note:** there is a parallel option set earlier (the `Query`/`Xic` subcommand parsers around lines 495-565 are separate); the spectra `--format` lives only in `RegularParametersParsing` (line 486+). Only edit the block at 529-533.
   197	
   198	---
   199	
   200	### `RawFileParser.cs` (modify, dispatch)
   201	
   202	**Analog:** the writer dispatch switch (lines 166-185).
   203	```csharp
   204	if (parseInput.OutputFormat != OutputFormat.None)
   205	{
   206	    SpectrumWriter spectrumWriter;
   207	    switch (parseInput.OutputFormat)
   208	    {
   209	        case OutputFormat.MGF:
   210	            spectrumWriter = new MgfSpectrumWriter(parseInput);
   211	            spectrumWriter.Write(rawFile, firstScanNumber, lastScanNumber);
   212	            break;
   213	        case OutputFormat.MzML:
   214	        case OutputFormat.IndexMzML:
   215	            spectrumWriter = new MzMlSpectrumWriter(parseInput);
   216	            spectrumWriter.Write(rawFile, firstScanNumber, lastScanNumber);
   217	            break;
   218	        case OutputFormat.Parquet:
   219	            spectrumWriter = new ParquetSpectrumWriter(parseInput);
   220	            spectrumWriter.Write(rawFile, firstScanNumber, lastScanNumber);
   221	            break;
   222	    }
   223	}
   224	```
   225	- **Copy:** add a new `case OutputFormat.MzPeak:` block in the same style as the `Parquet` case (lines 180-183): instantiate `new MzPeakSpectrumWriter(parseInput)`, assign to `spectrumWriter`, call `.Write(rawFile, firstScanNumber, lastScanNumber)`, `break`. `firstScanNumber`/`lastScanNumber` come from `RunHeaderEx.FirstSpectrum/LastSpectrum` (lines 150-151).
   226	- **Change:** none beyond the new case. Output path/extension is NOT derived here — it is set inside the writer via `ConfigureWriter(".mzpeak")` (or the writer's own `File.Create`), so RawFileParser stays format-agnostic.
   227	- **Imports:** `using ThermoRawFileParser.Writer;` already present (line 10) — `MzPeakSpectrumWriter` is in that namespace, so no new using needed.
   228	
   229	---
   230	
   231	## Shared Patterns
   232	
   233	### Error / warning accounting
   234	**Source:** `ParseInput.cs:161-169` (`NewError()` / `NewWarn()` increment counters) used throughout writers (`ParquetSpectrumWriter.cs:97,155,273`; `MgfSpectrumWriter.cs:68`).
   235	**Apply to:** every per-scan catch block in `MzPeakSpectrumWriter`. Tests assert `parseInput.Errors == 0` and `Warnings == 0` (WriterTests), so the new writer must keep both at zero on the clean `small.RAW`.
   236	
   237	### Logging
   238	**Source:** every writer declares `private static readonly ILog Log = LogManager.GetLogger(MethodBase.GetCurrentMethod().DeclaringType);` (`SpectrumWriter.cs:19-20`, `ParquetSpectrumWriter.cs:38-39`, `MgfSpectrumWriter.cs:14-15`).
   239	**Apply to:** `MzPeakSpectrumWriter` and any helper class that logs. `Log.Info` for scan-count, `Log.Error`+`Log.Debug` in catch, `Log.Debug` for row-group writes.
   240	
   241	### Output-path / extension derivation
   242	**Source:** `SpectrumWriter.ConfigureWriter` (`.cs:78-103`) + private `NormalizeFileName` (`.cs:105-128`). Path = `OutputFile ?? Path.Combine(OutputDirectory, RawFileNameWithoutExtension)`, extension appended/normalized, gzip handled.
   243	**Apply to:** the new writer. **Gap to resolve:** `ConfigureWriter` only special-cases `OutputFormat.Parquet` (line 88) for binary output; `MzPeak` must be added there OR the writer opens its own file stream (see writer section). The mzML/Parquet/MGF test-extension assertions (WriterTests `TestExtensionsNull/Full`) define the naming contract a Phase-4 mzPeak test will mirror (`small.mzpeak`).
   244	
   245	---
   246	
   247	## No Analog Found
   248	
   249	| Concern | Why no analog | Planner action |
   250	|---------|---------------|----------------|
   251	| Low-level Parquet.Net `ParquetSchema`/`DataColumn`/`ParquetWriter` for nested struct + list-of-struct + parallel nullable columns | All existing Parquet I/O uses the **high-level** `ParquetSerializer` POCO path (`ParquetSpectrumWriter.cs:57,106`). No low-level usage exists in the repo. | Use RESEARCH.md API snippets; this is the phase's primary spike (CONTEXT open questions 1-2). |
   252	| `ZipArchive` STORED container wrapping Parquet + `mzpeak_index.json` | No code in the repo emits a ZIP container; gzip is the only compression used (`SpectrumWriter.cs:99`). | New code; model JSON emission on existing `Newtonsoft.Json` usage (already referenced; see `XIC/JSONParser.cs`, `Writer/Metadata*.cs`). |
   253	| PARAM value-struct + CV-accession column-name helper | No existing struct/helper encodes the mzPeak PARAM shape or accession-in-column-name convention. CV handling exists only as `CVParamType` copy/compare (`Util/CVHelpers.cs`). | Net-new logic; copy only file placement/style from `Util/CVHelpers.cs` + `Writer/WriterUtil.cs`. |
   254	
   255	---
   256	
   257	## Test Pattern (Phase 4 reference)
   258	
   259	**Analog:** `ThermoRawFileParserTest/WriterTests.cs`, `TestParquetCentroid` (lines 416-445) — the closest existing test for a binary Parquet writer.
   260	```csharp
   261	[Test]
   262	public void TestParquetCentroid()
   263	{
   264	    var tempFilePath = Path.GetTempPath();
   265	    var testRawFile = Path.Combine(AppDomain.CurrentDomain.BaseDirectory, @"Data/small.RAW");
   266	    var parseInput = new ParseInput(testRawFile, null, tempFilePath, OutputFormat.Parquet);
   267	
   268	    RawFileParser.Parse(parseInput);
   269	    Assert.That(parseInput.Errors, Is.EqualTo(0));
   270	    Assert.That(parseInput.Warnings, Is.EqualTo(0));
   271	
   272	    var parquetFilePath = Path.Combine(tempFilePath, "small.mzparquet");
   273	    Assert.That(File.Exists(parquetFilePath));
   274	    using (var parquetReader = ParquetReader.CreateAsync(parquetFilePath).Result)
   275	    {
   276	        var groupReader = parquetReader.OpenRowGroupReader(0);
   277	        var schema = parquetReader.Schema;
   278	        var scanColumn = groupReader.ReadColumnAsync(schema.FindDataField("scan")).Result;
   279	        Assert.That(scanColumn.NumValues, Is.EqualTo(48520));
   280	        Assert.That(scanColumn.Statistics.DistinctCount, Is.EqualTo(48));
   281	    }
   282	    File.Delete(parquetFilePath);
   283	}
   284	```
   285	**Convention to follow for a Phase-4 mzPeak test:**
   286	- `[TestFixture]` class, `[Test]` methods, NUnit `Assert.That(...)` constraint style.
   287	- Input fixture: `Data/small.RAW` resolved via `AppDomain.CurrentDomain.BaseDirectory`; output to `Path.GetTempPath()`; clean up with `File.Delete` / `Directory.Delete`.
   288	- Construct `new ParseInput(testRawFile, null, tempFilePath, OutputFormat.MzPeak)` and drive via `RawFileParser.Parse(parseInput)` (full integration, not the writer in isolation).
   289	- Assert `parseInput.Errors == 0` and `Warnings == 0`, then `File.Exists("small.mzpeak")`.
   290	- **Change for mzPeak:** open the produced `.mzpeak` as a `ZipArchive`, read the Parquet entry with `ParquetReader` (as above) and/or assert `mzpeak_index.json` is present. The CONTEXT success gate ("reference Python reader opens it") is an out-of-process check — that belongs in a script/CI step, not necessarily this NUnit test; the NUnit test should at minimum confirm a STORED ZIP with the expected entries.
   291	- Test project excludes itself from the main build (`csproj` lines 31-33) and references NUnit + Parquet directly (WriterTests `using NUnit.Framework; using Parquet;`).
   292	
