refs/_findings/mzpeak_mapping_report.md:219:**Goal:** Guarantee `point.mz` column is ascending (mzPeak spec `sorting_rank: 0` + Parquet range index requirement).
refs/_findings/mzpeak_mapping_report.md:231:     - Emit `mzml2mzpeak_sort_peaks` data_processing step (once per file if any reordered)
refs/_findings/mzpeak_mapping_report.md:236:- **Representation::Profile** → NO peak list attached → writer routes to `spectra_data`
refs/_findings/mzpeak_mapping_report.md:238:- **Representation::Unknown** → NO peak list → routes to `spectra_data`
refs/_findings/mzpeak_mapping_report.md:240:**Why explicit peak list for centroid?** Reference writer's peaks facet only recognizes canonical `CentroidPeak` schema (m/z f64 + intensity f32 per mzpeaks crate). Raw arrays with dtype-suffixed names (`mz_f64`/`intensity_f32`) don't map into peaks facet, so values serialize as NULL without the peak list.
refs/_findings/mzpeak_mapping_report.md:244:- **Write:** Nested struct `precursor` (first precursor; multiple precursors compressed to one in mzPeak v0.9)
